  Name: Eurofighter Typhoon
  Information: The Eurofighter Typhoon is a highly agile, twin-engine, canard-delta
    wing, multirole fighter developed by a European consortium (Airbus, BAE Systems,
    Leonardo). Renowned for its "swing-role" capability, it excels in both air-to-air
    and precision strike missions. The jet is powered by two EJ200 engines providing
    a high thrust-to-weight ratio, reaching speeds of Mach 2.0+.
